  <asx:values>
   <VSEOCLASS>
    <CLSNAME>ZCL_EXCEL_FIELDCAT_CONVERTER</CLSNAME>
    <LANGU>E</LANGU>
    <DESCRIPT>Convert Field Catalogue</DESCRIPT>
    <STATE>1</STATE>
    <CLSCCINCL>X</CLSCCINCL>
    <FIXPT>X</FIXPT>
    <UNICODE>X</UNICODE>
   </VSEOCLASS>
   <LINES>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>U1</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>&amp;FUNCTIONALITY&amp;</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>We have a large number of existing reports which use the</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>REUSE_ALV_LIST_DISPLAY function module.</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>We desire to send these via emails in the background, and allow the user</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>to download them as excel spreadsheets.</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>The easy way would be to converet the existing reports to CL_SALV_TABLE.</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>This is not reallyviable as that would break the users existing variants</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>in production, and to be frank CL_SALV_TABLE often has less</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>functionality than the older technologies.</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>For new things we will use CL_SALV_TABLE where possible.  For existing</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>reports a workaround is just prior to emailing the data in the</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>background, we create an instance of CL_SALV_TABLE and then converet the</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>field catalouge, sort catalouge etc  from the REUSE_ALV_LIST_DISPLAY</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>into something CL_SALV_TABLE can work with.</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>Then we are laughing, we can use the ABAP2XLS class to converet the</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>CL_SALV_TABLE_OBJECT to a spreadsheet with settings based on the</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDLINE>variant.</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>U1</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>&amp;RELATIONS&amp;</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>U1</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>&amp;EXAMPLE&amp;</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>U1</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>&amp;HINTS&amp;</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>U1</TDFORMAT>
     <TDLINE>&amp;FURTHER_SOURCES_OF_INF&amp;</TDLINE>
    </TLINE>
    <TLINE>
     <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
    </TLINE>
   </LINES>
